# Multi-Variant, Cascading, Branch-Child & Repeatable Admin Fields

This codebase has a non-obvious admin → snapshot → resolver pipeline for:

1. **Same-label variants** — one logical field (e.g. "Make") with multiple admin
   rows scoped to different categories (`pcar`, `solo`, `commvehicle`).
2. **Cascading 2+ level fields** — a parent option (e.g. `Make = Hyundai`)
   that exposes nested children (e.g. `Model`).
3. **Boolean-branch children** — a boolean field (e.g. "No Claims Bonus?") with
   `meta.booleanChildren.{true,false}[]` exposing nested fields.
4. **Repeatable rows** — `inputType: "repeatable"` admin fields stored as arrays
   of row objects, addressed on the PDF via `__r<N>__<childKey>`.
5. **Select option labels** — snapshots store option `value`s
   (`"hkonly"`, `"fleet"`); PDFs must render option `label`s (`"Hong Kong Only"`).

If your task touches **any** of the following, STOP and read
[`.cursor/skills/multi-variant-fields/SKILL.md`](mdc:.cursor/skills/multi-variant-fields/SKILL.md)
**before** writing code:

- Adding/editing fields with the same label across vehicle / insured / package categories
- Adding cascading children under a `form_options.meta.options[].children` entry
- Adding `meta.booleanChildren.{true,false}[]` configurations
- Adding `inputType: "repeatable"` fields (top-level OR nested inside boolean branches)
- Editing `lib/pdf/build-context.ts` `loadPackageFieldVariants`
- Editing `lib/field-resolver.ts` `resolveByLabelVariant` / `resolvePackage` / `resolveInsuredPrimaryId` / `translateOptionValue` / `findVariantForKey`
- Editing `components/admin/pdf-templates/PdfTemplateEditor.tsx` `buildPackageSectionTemplate` / `SYNTHETIC_FIELDS_BY_SOURCE` / the form_options loader
- Working with snapshot keys matching `__opt_*__c[0-9]` / `__true__c[0-9]` / `__false__c[0-9]` / `__r[0-9]+__` / `__byLabel__*`
- Touching the wizard form-name template at `app/(dashboard)/policies/new/page.tsx` (boolean branch ~L822, repeatable row ~L908, top-level ~L121)
- Diagnosing "PDF shows raw `true` / `false` / a slug like `hkonly` / `[object Object]` / wrong driver row / empty 2nd–4th driver column"

## The 30-second cheatsheet

| Concern | Pattern | Don't do |
|---|---|---|
| Same-label admin fields | Resolver auto-routes via `__byLabel__<slug>` and category match | Don't place a category-locked key (e.g. `commake`) directly on a PDF |
| Cascading child snapshot key | `${parentKey}__opt_${optionValue}__c${childIndex}` (single `c`) | NOT `__sc${idx}` — that's a dead path |
| Boolean-branch child snapshot key | `${parentKey}__${branch}__c${childIndex}` where branch = `"true"`/`"false"` | Don't reinvent the suffix; matches wizard form names exactly |
| Boolean parent placed on PDF | Resolver smart-routes to `${key}__${branch}__c0` and translates options | Don't render `"true"`/`"false"` — Pattern D in the skill exists for this |
| Repeatable row snapshot key | Stored as an ARRAY at `vals[parent]`; PDF addresses via `${parent}__r${N}__${childKey}` | NOT a flat `${parent}__r${N}__${childKey}` snapshot key — `__r<N>__` is resolver-side synthetic |
| Repeatable inside a boolean branch | Combines: `${parent}__${branch}__c${idx}__r${N}__${childKey}` | Don't try to flatten — let the resolver compose the two patterns |
| Select option value → label | Variant carries `options[]`; resolver calls `translateOptionValue` | Don't hard-code label maps; load from `meta.options` |
| Synthetic UI field (Display Name, Primary ID, Make, Model) | `synthetic: true` shows the green **Auto** badge | Don't drop the flag or admins can't tell it auto-routes |
| Tenant-specific ID fields | Add to `PERSONAL_ID_KEYS` / `COMPANY_ID_KEYS` fallback chain in `field-resolver.ts` | Don't hard-code one tenant's choice (e.g. `brNumber` only) |

If anything above is unclear, the skill has the full contract, examples, and
a verification recipe you can run against the live DB.
